{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We release the evaluation data consisting of 2,426 queries and 225,618 passages.",
    "We evaluate the final output of Scholar QA on the ScholarQA-CS dataset which consists of expertannotated rubrics for 100 Computer Science research questions.",
    "The question-specific expert rubrics account for 60% of the final score, while the rest is computed based on global metrics of length, expertise and citations.",
    "We use GPT-4o (Hurst et al., 2024) as a judge with the utility provided by Asai et al. (2024) for automatic evaluation and compare against several baselines.",
    "As shown in Table 2, our system outperforms popular LLMs: Llama 3.1 (Dubey et al., 2024), GPT 4.1 and Claude Sonnet 3.7 (Anthropic, 2024)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We use GPT-4o (Hurst et al., 2024) as a judge with the utility provided by Asai et al. (2024) for automatic evaluation and compare against several baselines.",
